AttributeList.Text:
How to operate and control the roller: Roller is controled by inputs in WebDB: Mode, SetSpeed, Direction, OffsetSpeed. To start the roller use Start_Roller and to stop use Stop_Roller.
Mode descriptions: 0 - Controlling the roller by just turning it ON/OFF 1 - Basic speed control of the roller with 0-100% 2 - Direct speed control based on Y axis velocity. Not useful for printing, but might help in the development process to observe roller system inertia. 3 - Setting relative surface velocity (powder to roller). There is no control loop. Could be used for testing the feature before evaluating.
E-STOP - always check!
Mode 1; Input to PWM Conversion Manual
Mode 2; Input to PWM Conversion Automatic Y velocity = Roller velocity
Mode 3; Input to PWM Conversion Setting Speed Difference according to the Y velocity
